  "text": "We also investigate silting-discreteness for a particularly important class of triangulated categories. We call an ST-pair (C, D) a (d + 1)-Calabi-Yau pair (Definition 8.1) if C ⊇ D and there is a bifunctorial isomorphism D Hom(X, Y ) ≃ Hom (Y, X[d + 1] ) for X ∈ D and Y ∈ C. In this case, we give a characterisation of silting-discreteness for C using cluster-tilting theory for the cluster category C/D ( [CITATION_1] Section 5.3] ). We apply this result to two important classes of dg algebras: the complete Ginzburg dg algebras and (d + 1)-derived preprojective algebras, which are examples of deformed Calabi-Yau completions in the sense of [K2] . Notation and convention. Throughout this paper let K be a field and denote the K-dual by D = Hom K (−, K). Let T be a K-linear additive category. We say that T is Hom-finite if all morphism spaces of T are finite-dimensional over K. We say that T is idempotent complete if any idempotent e : M → M in T arises from a direct sum decomposition M ≃ im(e) ⊕ ker(e). We say that T is Krull-Schmidt if every object M of T is isomorphic to M 1 ⊕ . . . ⊕ M n with M 1 , . . . , M n having local endomorphism algebras. For example, any Hom-finite K-linear abelian category is Krull-Schmidt (by [At, Theorem 1] ). The object M is said to be basic if in the above decomposition M 1 ⊕ . . . ⊕ M n the objects M 1 , . . . , M n are pairwise non-isomorphic. In this case, we denote |M | = n.",
