      "span_text": "We call an ST-pair (C, D) a (d + 1)-Calabi-Yau pair (Definition 8.1) if C ⊇ D and there is a bifunctorial isomorphism D Hom(X, Y ) ≃ Hom (Y, X[d + 1] ) for X ∈ D and Y ∈ C. In this case, we give a characterisation of silting-discreteness for C using cluster-tilting theory for the cluster category C/D (  Section 5.3] ).",
